Ok since y’all asked here’s the very quick version of how I lost my passport when I was 16… 

At some point ( we are pretty sure it happened when we were exchanging money) my I.D was never given back. 

By the time I realized what happened it was the next day 🥴 I told the mom of the family I was staying with who realized yup it was definitely lost.

At this point even though we retraced our steps it was long gone. 

Since I needed to travel home I had to come clean and tell my parents who were back in the U.S. what happened. 

The next thing I knew my parents were literally in Mexico hunting me down because they were over it and had kinda lost faith in the family that was supposed to be “responsible” for me 😅

They were able to fly me back with proof of their American citizenship and a xerox copy of my stolen passport which we were in the process of getting replaced . 

So yeah it was pretty crazy and might explain my moms trust issues but I made it back and we are actually able to laugh about it now 😅
